0
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,360
HENRY LOUIS GATES JR.: You have a true north all your own.

1
00:00:03,360 --> 00:00:08,400
As you continue your journey, I urge you to shift your gaze inward.

2
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,620
Don't compare yourself to other people.

3
00:00:10,620 --> 00:00:13,580
You can learn from others, but find the courage

4
00:00:13,580 --> 00:00:17,520
to tailor your decisions to your own circumstances.

5
00:00:17,520 --> 00:00:21,500
Let your decisions serve the real you.

6
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:26,180
You can stay true to yourself by using the tools and mindsets that we've

7
00:00:26,180 --> 00:00:28,520
discussed throughout this course.

8
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:31,430
Embrace your multiple identities.

9
00:00:31,430 --> 00:00:35,150
Set boundaries to protect yourself.

10
00:00:35,150 --> 00:00:38,060
Develop a healthy attitude to conflict.

11
00:00:38,060 --> 00:00:39,750
Ask for help.

12
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:42,600
Build authentic relationships.

13
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:46,460
Take ownership of the stereotypes and biases

14
00:00:46,460 --> 00:00:50,630
that influence how others perceive you.

15
00:00:50,630 --> 00:00:56,240
Be strategic and intentional about how you present yourself in the world.

16
00:00:56,240 --> 00:01:00,230
As you tune into your authentic self, you'll also

17
00:01:00,230 --> 00:01:03,260
become more cognizant of your purpose.

18
00:01:03,260 --> 00:01:07,700
The same strategies that we've discussed in this course

19
00:01:07,700 --> 00:01:09,950
will help you take the next steps in your life

20
00:01:09,950 --> 00:01:13,820
and career towards relationships and activities

21
00:01:13,820 --> 00:01:16,860
that have the deepest meaning for you.

22
00:01:16,860 --> 00:01:24,140
Crystallizing your purpose is a long, complex, and invigorating journey,

23
00:01:24,140 --> 00:01:31,540
but it starts with a curious mindset about what feels right to you.

